The Adamawa State Governor, Ahmadu Umaru Fintiri, Thursday inspected Bachure township road project awarded to Batco CMC company. The 18 km road and other projects in the state was awarded at over N5 billion. The Bachure 3.8 kilometers is one of the critical road projects, the Governor had promised the community during electioneering campaign. Fintiri said he was at the site to see the progress of the work and expressed appreciation on the pace and quality of the work. The contractor handling the project added that, the company segmented the projects in phases and vowed to complete every three roads in four months in order to meet up with the timeline stipulated in the contractual agreement. When completed the Bachuri community will have a lease of life, stressing that his administration will continue to do its best towards modernizing the state capital to boost the socio-economic activities of the state. The Governor was accompanied by the Secretary to the State Government (SSG), Malam Bashiru Ahmad among other senior government officials who  was taking round the project by the Permanent Secretary Ministry of Works and Energy Development Engr. Suleiman Mohammed. 